BirthEvidence.label: Birth evidence
BirthEvidence.description: Official document or data proving the Birth of a Child.

BirthEvidence/Identifier.label: Identifier
BirthEvidence/Identifier.description: An unambiguous reference to the Birth Evidence.

BirthEvidence/IssueDate.label: Issue date
BirthEvidence/IssueDate.description: The most recent date on which the Birth Evidence instance was issued.

BirthEvidence/IssuingAuthority.label: Issuing authority
BirthEvidence/IssuingAuthority.description: A Public Organisation with official authority in charge of issuing the Birth Evidence.

BirthEvidence/IssuingPlace.label: Issuing place
BirthEvidence/IssuingPlace.description: The Location where the Birth Evidence was issued.

BirthEvidence/CertifiesBirth.label: Certifies birth
BirthEvidence/CertifiesBirth.description: Attesting in a formal way that the Birth is true.

BirthEvidence/CertifiesBirth/Child.label: Child
BirthEvidence/CertifiesBirth/Child.description: The Person who is born at the Birth. A Person of any age, who is a son or daughter.

BirthEvidence/CertifiesBirth/Parent.label: Parent
BirthEvidence/CertifiesBirth/Parent.description: The Parent of the Child. One of the two Persons who are jointly the cause of the Child's Birth, i.e. natural parent.

LocationAddress/AdminUnitL2.label: Admin unit level 2
LocationAddress/AdminUnitL2.description: The region of the address, usually a county, state or other such area that typically encompasses several localities.

LocationAddress/AdminUnitL1.label: Admin unit level 1
LocationAddress/AdminUnitL1.description: The uppermost administrative unit for the address, almost always a country. Best practice is to use the ISO 3166-1 code.

LocationAddress/PoBox.label: PoBox
LocationAddress/PoBox.description: The Post Office Box number. INSPIRE's name for this is 'postalDeliveryIdentifier' for which it uses the locator designator property with a type attribute of that name. This vocabulary separates out the Post Office Box for greater independence of technology.

LocationAddress/Thoroughfare.label: Thoroughface
LocationAddress/Thoroughfare.description: Quoting from the INSPIRE guidelines, a thoroughfare is: 'an address component that represents the name of a passage or way through from one location to another. A thoroughfare is not necessarily a road, it might be a waterway or some other feature.

LocationAddress/LocatorDesignator.label: Locator designator
LocationAddress/LocatorDesignator.description: The locator designator is defined by the INSPIRE guidelines as 'a number or a sequence of characters that uniquely identifies the locator within the relevant scope(s). The full identification of the locator could include one or more locator designators.' In simpler terms, this is the building number, apartment number, etc. For an address such as 'Flat 3, 17 Bridge Street', the locator is 'flat 3, 17.'

LocationAddress/LocatorName.label: Locator name
LocationAddress/LocatorName.description: Based on the INSPIRE guidelines, locator name is defined as: 'Proper noun(s) applied to the real world entity identified by the locator. The locator name could be the name of the property or complex, of the building or part of the building, or it could be the name of a room inside a building. The key difference between a locator and a locator name is that the latter is a proper name and is unlikely to include digits. For example, 'Shumann, Berlaymont' is a meeting room within the European Commission headquarters for which locator name is more appropriate than locator.

LocationAddress/AddressArea.label: Address area
LocationAddress/AddressArea.description: Taking the definition from INSPIRE, the address area is: the name or names of a geographic area or locality that groups a number of addressable objects for addressing purposes, without being an administrative unit.' This would typically be part of a city, a neighbourhood or village.

LocationAddress/PostName.label: Post name
LocationAddress/PostName.description: The key postal division of the address, usually the city. (INSPIRE's definition is 'One or more names created and maintained for postal purposes to identify a subdivision of addresses and postal delivery points.)

LocationAddress/PostCode.label: Post code
LocationAddress/PostCode.description: The post code (a.k.a postal code, zip code etc.). Post codes are common elements in many countries' postal address systems.

CountryEnum.description: ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 codes are three-letter country codes defined in ISO 3166-1, part of the ISO 3166 standard published by the International Organization for Standardization, to represent countries, dependent territories, and special areas of geographical interest.

CountryEnum/PCI.label: Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands

CountryEnum/SGS.label: South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands

CountryEnum/SHN.label: Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha

Identifier.label: Identifier
Identifier.description: The Identifier class allows an identifier to be given as well as information about which authority issued it and, if needed, when.

Identifier/IdentifierType.label: Identifier Type
Identifier/IdentifierType.description: The type of identifier issued (if the authority issues more than one type of identifier).

Identifier/IssueDate.label: Issue Date
Identifier/IssueDate.description: The date on which it was issued

Identifier/IssuingAuthority.label: Issuing Authority
Identifier/IssuingAuthority.description: The name of the issuing agency

Jurisdiction/Identifier.label: Identifier
Jurisdiction/Identifier.description: The value for the id property is a URI for that Jurisdiction.

Jurisdiction/Name.label: Name
Jurisdiction/Name.description: The name is simply a string that identifies the Jurisdiction, typically a country, with or without a language tag.

Person.label: Person
Person.description: An individual natural person who may be dead or alive, but not imaginary.

Person/DateOfBirth.label: Date of birth
Person/DateOfBirth.description: The day on which the person was born.

Person/DateOfBirth/Year.label: Year
Person/DateOfBirth/Year.description: A gregorian calendar year. The value space of Year is the set of Gregorian calendar years as defined in § 5.2.1 of ISO 8601. Specifically, it is a set of one-year long, non-periodic instances e.g. lexical 1999 to represent the whole year 1999, independent of how many months and days this year has.

Person/DateOfBirth/Month.label: Month
Person/DateOfBirth/Month.description: A gregorian month that recurs every year. The value space of Month is the space of a set of calendar months as defined in § 3 of ISO 8601. Specifically, it is a set of one-month long, yearly periodic instances.

Person/DateOfBirth/Day.label: Day
Person/DateOfBirth/Day.description: A gregorian day that recurs, specifically a day of the month such as the 5th of the month. The value space of Day is the space of a set of calendar dates as defined in § 3 of ISO 8601. Specifically, it is a set of one-day long, monthly periodic instances.

Person/Gender.label: Gender
Person/Gender.description: The chromosomal state, and reproductive organs and structures of a Person that allows them to be distinguished as female or male or undetermined.

Person/PlaceOfBirth.label: Place of birth
Person/PlaceOfBirth.description: The Location where the person was born.

Person/PersonName.label: Person name
Person/PersonName.description: The family name and given name of a Person. At least one of the two must exist.

Person/PersonName/FamilyName.label: Family name
Person/PersonName/FamilyName.description: A family name is usually shared by members of a family. This attribute also carries prefixes or suffixes which are part of the family name, e.g. 'de Boer', 'van de Putte', 'von und zu Orlow'. Multiple family names, such as are commonly found in Hispanic countries, are recorded in the single family name field so that, for example, Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra's Family Name would be recorded as 'de Cervantes Saavedra'.

Person/PersonName/GivenName.label: Given name
Person/PersonName/GivenName.description: A given name, or multiple given names, are the denominator(s) that identify an individual within a family. These are given to a Person by his or her parents at birth or may be legally recognised as 'given names' through a formal process. All given names are ordered in one field so that, for example, the given name for Johann Sebastian Bach is 'Johann Sebastian'.

Person/Identifier.label: Identifier
Person/Identifier.description: The identifier relation is used to link a Person to any formally issued Identifier for that Person.

Person/Citizenship.label: Citizenship
Person/Citizenship.description: The citizenship relationship links a Person to a Jurisdiction that has conferred citizenship rights on the individual such as the right to vote, to receive certain protection from the community or the issuance of a passport.

PersonGenderEnum/Female.label: Female
PersonGenderEnum/Female.description: The concept FEMALE is used for representing the human sexes in the context of interchange of information in the social sciences domain.

PersonGenderEnum/Male.label: Male
PersonGenderEnum/Male.description: The concept MALE is used for representing the human sexes in the context of interchange of information in the social sciences domain.

PersonGenderEnum/NAP.label: Not applicable
PersonGenderEnum/NAP.description: The concept NOT APPLICABLE is used in the context of interchange of information in the social sciences domain when none of the sexes can be represented.

PersonGenderEnum/NKN.label: Not known
PersonGenderEnum/NKN.description: The concept NOT KNOWN is used in the context of interchange of information in the social sciences domain when the human sex is unkown.

PersonGenderEnum/NST.label: Not stated
PersonGenderEnum/NST.description: The concept NOT STATED is used in the context of interchange of information in the social sciences domain when the human sex is not stated.

PublicOrganisation/Identifier.label: Identifier
PublicOrganisation/Identifier.description: Many organisations are referred to by an acronym or some other identifier. For example, among the EU institutions, the ECB is the identifier for the European Central Bank, OLAF for the European AntiN/AFraud Office, and so on. These are formally recognised by the European Commission which provides a list of such acronyms. Analogous lists should be used in other contexts.

PublicOrganisation/PrefLabel.label: Preferred label
PublicOrganisation/PrefLabel.description: As defined in the ORG Ontology, a preferred label is used to provide the primary, legally recognised name of the organisation. An organisation may only have one such name in any given language. Primary names may be provided in multiple languages with multiple instances of the preferred label property.

UDT/Text.label: Text
UDT/Text.description: A character string (i.e. a finite set of characters), generally in the form of words of a language.

UDT/Text/@LanguageID.label: Language ID
UDT/Text/@LanguageID.description: The identifier of the language used in the content component.

UDT/Text/@LanguageLocaleID.label: Language Locale ID
UDT/Text/@LanguageLocaleID.description: The identification of the locale of the language.

UDT/Date.label: Date
UDT/Date.description: One calendar day according the Gregorian calendar.

UDT/Name.label: Name
UDT/Name.description: A character string that constitutes the distinctive designation of a person, place, thing or concept.

UDT/Identifier.label: Identifier
UDT/Identifier.description: A character string to identify and distinguish uniquely, one instance of an object in an identification scheme from all other objects in the same scheme together with relevant supplementary information.

UDT/Identifier/@schemeID.label: Scheme ID
UDT/Identifier/@schemeID.description: The identification of the identification scheme.

UDT/Identifier/@schemeName.label: Scheme Name
UDT/Identifier/@schemeName.description: The name of the identification scheme.

UDT/Identifier/@schemeAgencyID.label: Scheme Agency ID
UDT/Identifier/@schemeAgencyID.description: The identification of the agency that maintains the identification scheme.

UDT/Identifier/@schemeAgencyName.label: Scheme Agency Name
UDT/Identifier/@schemeAgencyName.description: The name of the agency that maintains the identification scheme.

UDT/Identifier/@schemeVersionID.label: Scheme Version ID
UDT/Identifier/@schemeVersionID.description: The version of the identification scheme.

UDT/Identifier/@schemeDataURI.label: Scheme Data URI
UDT/Identifier/@schemeDataURI.description: The Uniform Resource Identifier that identifies where the identification scheme data is located.

UDT/Identifier/@schemeURI.label: Scheme URI
UDT/Identifier/@schemeURI.description: The Uniform Resource Identifier that identifies where the identification scheme is located.

PersonMaritalStatusEnum/DivorcedPerson.label: Divorced person
PersonMaritalStatusEnum/DivorcedPerson.description: A person marital status : divorced person

PersonMaritalStatusEnum/SeparatedPerson.label: Separated person
PersonMaritalStatusEnum/SeparatedPerson.description: A person marital status: separated person

PersonMaritalStatusEnum/SingleParent.label: Single parent
PersonMaritalStatusEnum/SingleParent.description: A person marital status: single parent

PersonMaritalStatusEnum/UnmarriedPerson.label: Unmarried person
PersonMaritalStatusEnum/UnmarriedPerson.description: A person marital status: unmarried person

MarriageEvidence.label: Marriage evidence
MarriageEvidence.description: Official document or data proving the Marriage of two Persons.

MarriageEvidence/Identifier.label: Identifier
MarriageEvidence/Identifier.description: An unambiguous reference to the Marriage Evidence.

MarriageEvidence/IssueDate.label: Issue date
MarriageEvidence/IssueDate.description: The most recent date on which the MarriageEvidence instance was issued.

MarriageEvidence/IssuingAuthority.label: Issuing authority
MarriageEvidence/IssuingAuthority.description: A Public Organisation with official authority in charge of issuing the Marriage Evidence.

MarriageEvidence/IssuingPlace.label: Issuing place
MarriageEvidence/IssuingPlace.description: The Location where the Marriage Evidence was issued.

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage.label: Certifies marriage
MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage.description: Attesting in a formal way that the Marriage is true.

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/DateO.label: Date of marriage
MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/DateO.description: The date on which the Marriage took place.

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/Spous.description: The gender of an individual should be recorded using a controlled vocabulary that is appropriate for the specific context. In some cases the chromosomal or physical state of an individual will be more important than the gender that they express, in others the reverse will be true. What is always important is that the controlled vocabulary used to describe an individual's gender is stated explicitly.

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/Spous.label: Family name after marriage
MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/Spous.description: This property contains the family name after the Marriage of the Person.

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/Spous.label: Family name before marriage
MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/Spous.description: This property contains the family name before the Marriage of the Person.

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/Spous.label: Marital status before marriage
MarriageEvidence/CertifiesMarriage/Spous.description: Situation with regard to whether a Person was single, married, separated, divorced or widowed.

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesEndOfMarriage.label: End of marriage
MarriageEvidence/CertifiesEndOfMarriage.description: In case of divorce, this property includes information on the end of marriage

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesEndOfMarriage/.label: Date of end of marriage
MarriageEvidence/CertifiesEndOfMarriage/.description: Date of the end of marriage

MarriageEvidence/CertifiesEndOfMarriage/.label: Cause
MarriageEvidence/CertifiesEndOfMarriage/.description: Cause of the end of marriage.
